## Mining Method

**LAMMPS: fully hand-authored.** There is no mining script. The 4 tasks were written manually
to cover distinct physics scenarios (simple MD, crack mechanics, electrostatics/constraints).
No equivalent of `example_pairs.jsonl` exists.

The only automated indexing in the LAMMPS plugin is `build_lammps_vector_db.py` ‚Üí `_in_files()`,
which recursively scans the LAMMPS source `examples/` tree for any file named `in.*` or `*.in`
and indexes them into the `lammps_technical` ChromaDB collection ‚Äî but that is purely for RAG
retrieval, not for building eval tasks.

### GEOS comparison ‚Äî key differences

| Dimension | GEOS | LAMMPS |
|---|---|---|
| Task origin | Mined from RST tutorial pages in GEOS docs | Hand-authored by developer |
| Source mapping | `example_pairs.jsonl` (task_id ‚Üí RST path) | None |
| Contamination blocking | GT XML basenames + variant siblings + source RST page | None (no contamination module for LAMMPS) |
| Variant expansion | 9 XML suffix patterns (`_base`, `_smoke`, `_benchmark`, etc.) | N/A ‚Äî `.in` files have no naming convention for variants |
| GT files | Actual files from GEOS source tree | Manually written reference scripts |
| Scale | Enough tasks for a full matrix eval | 4 tasks |

